## 3. ARCHITECTURAL SAFETY

### Do not rewrite working game logic

**Unless the user explicitly asks**, do not refactor, rename, or "clean up":

- Core game components: `GeographyGame.tsx`, `TapGame.tsx`, `HuntGame.tsx`
- Globe/map stack: `WorldMap.tsx`, `TapGlobe.tsx`, `HuntGlobe.tsx`, `globe-polygon-styles.ts`
- Daily engine: `daily-engine.ts`, `daily-hunt.ts`, `daily-locations.ts`, border graph modules
- Scoring/progress: `sweep-progress.ts`, `tap-scoring.ts`, `hunt-scoring.ts`, `hunt-guess.ts`

Bug fixes and **minimal, targeted diffs** are fine. Drive-by abstraction, file splits, or logic rewrites are not.

### Match existing structure

```
src/
  app/(game)/     Sweep, Tap, Hunt routes + shared game layout
  app/api/        Route handlers only — delegate to src/lib/server/
  components/game/   In-round UI (HUD, results, modals, mode clients)
  components/map/    Globe rendering
  components/menu/   Profile, friends, rankings, settings
  components/retention/  Streaks, heatmap (post-MVP)
  components/growth/     Archive, compare (monetization)
  lib/            Client-safe game logic, hooks, storage
  lib/server/     Server-only validation, Supabase admin, daily engine
  contexts/       Auth, globe shell
  data/           Static JSON datasets (countries, locations, hunt tiers)
```

- New API routes → `src/app/api/<area>/route.ts`, logic in `src/lib/server/`.
- New client hooks → `src/lib/use-*.ts`.
- New game UI → `src/components/game/` (or `menu/` / `retention/` if appropriate).
- Types → `src/types/`.

### Dependencies & data

- Do not replace `countries.json`, TopoJSON assets, or the border graph without explicit approval — they are tuned for gameplay.
- Supabase schema changes require a new file in `supabase/migrations/`; never edit old migrations in place.
- Run `npm test` and `npm run validate-data` when touching game logic or datasets.

### Scope discipline

- One concern per change. No bundling unrelated features, drive-by formatting, or speculative "improvements."
- Prefer extending existing functions over parallel implementations.

---

## 4. HUMAN COPY WRITING

All user-facing text — HUD labels, modals, toasts, errors, emails, share lines, empty states, button labels — must sound like a **real person** talking to a friend who likes maps. Not a press release. Not an AI blog post.

### Voice

- **Short sentences.** Get to the point.
- **Second person** ("you") when instructing; **first person plural** ("we") sparingly for the brand.
- **Concrete verbs:** name, tap, sweep, guess, share — not "engage with" or "leverage."
- Light humor is welcome; smugness and jargon are not.
- Match the tone of existing copy in `WelcomeModal.tsx`, `ShareResult.tsx`, and result screens.

### Good vs bad

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|--------|
| "One wrong answer ends the run." | "An incorrect response will terminate your session." |
| "Today's puzzles are ready." | "We're excited to unveil today's challenges!" |
| "Nice sweep — Tap's waiting." | "Congratulations on completing the Sweep mode experience." |
| "Couldn't save your score. Try again." | "We encountered an issue processing your submission." |

### Banned words and patterns

Never use these (and close cousins): **delve**, **testament**, **foster**, **revolutionize**, **landscape** (metaphorical), **tapestry**, **journey** (metaphorical), **robust**, **seamless**, **cutting-edge**, **game-changer**, **dive in**, **unlock**, **elevate**, **empower**, **harness**, **navigate** (metaphorical), **in today's fast-paced world**.

Also avoid:

- Exclamation marks in error messages
- "Oops!" / "Uh oh!" unless the moment is genuinely light
- Emoji in core game UI (share text may use sparingly if already established)
- Title Case Every Word In Sentences

### Copy locations checklist

When adding features, update copy in the same PR for: modal title + body, button labels, `aria-label`s, share strings (`share-result.ts`, `tap-share-result.ts`, `hunt-share-result.ts`), API email HTML (`cron/daily-email`), and static pages (`about`, `classroom`, legal pages).

Brand name: **Daily Globe Games** (compact HUD may use **Daily Globe**). Domain: `dailyglobegames.com`.
